13/07/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador for War Crimes Issues Pierre-Richard Prosper met on Tuesday (12 July) with the members of BiH tripartite presidency in Sarajevo. 
All agreed on the importance of capturing those indicted for war crimes, especially Ratko Mladic and Radovan Karadzic. 
Prosper also paid a visit to the BiH court and prosecution, to learn about the election procedures for judges, the court's technical capacities and other issues. 
He vowed to do all he could to ensure indictees stand trial in the countries where they allegedly committed the crimes. 
(Dnevni Avaz - 13/07/05; PBS BiH, FENA - 12/07/05)
